				 ICSE, ISC shift in 08 

 A STAFF REPORTER
																								The revised syllabi of the ICSE and ISC will take effect from next year. The new curricula will be posted on the Internet on December 31.
																								An official of the Council for Indian School Certificate Examinations, which conducts the two exams, said the syllabi have been restructured to enable the students to prepare for the all-India entrance tests along with the school- leaving one.
																								More than 1,500 schools in the country are affiliated to the council.
																								The new syllabi are relevant to competitive exams like pre-medical tests and IIT-JEE and other engineering entrance tests. The changes are in accordance with the National Curriculum Framework 2005, said Gerry Arathoon, the additional secretary and acting chief executive officer of the council.
																								The students of classes IX and XI will follow the new syllabi from next year.

